This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D shape modeling from a single image. The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the creation of a large-scale dataset, which could place it in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of behavioral studies to calibrate evaluation criteria, which suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of multi-task learning, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
